But, Twilight!

261
00:10:37,210 --> 00:10:39,400
Eh!
This is my decision.

262
00:10:39,530 --> 00:10:41,110
And I'm gonna make it
on my own.

263
00:10:41,230 --> 00:10:43,610
And I certainly can't think
straight with all this noise.

264
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:44,510
[ Stomach grumbling ]

265
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:46,080
Not to mention hunger.

266
00:10:46,460 --> 00:10:47,900
Now go on!
Shoo!

267
00:10:48,150 --> 00:10:51,200
[ All grumbling ]

268
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:54,560
And don't worry!
I'll figure this out!

269
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:57,290
Somehow.

270
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:02,960
Aw, Spike,
what am I gonna do?

271
00:11:03,410 --> 00:11:05,730
All five of my best friends
have really good reasons

272
00:11:05,810 --> 00:11:06,860
To go to the gala.

273
00:11:07,290 --> 00:11:09,580
Applejack
or Rainbow Dash?

274
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,300
Pinkie Pie or Fluttershy?
Rarity?

275
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:14,560
Oh, who should
go with me?

276
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:16,540
[ Stomach grumbling ]

277
00:11:17,530 --> 00:11:19,110
Waiter:
have you made your decision?

278
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:20,760
I can't decide!

279
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:23,400
Twilight, he just wants
to take your order.

280
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:24,480
Oh.

281
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,400
I would love
a daffodil-And-Daisy sandwich.

282
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,860
Do you have
any rubies?

283
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:30,350
No?

284
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:32,510
Okay.
I'll have the hay fries.

285
00:11:32,670 --> 00:11:33,900
Extra crispy!

286
00:11:34,230 --> 00:11:35,450
What do you think,
Spike?

287
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,490
I think we have to try
another restaurant.

288
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:39,390
I mean,
I like grass just fine,

289
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:41,800
But would it hurt anybody
to offer some gemstones?

290
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:44,800
I mean about the gala and the
ticket and who I should take.

291
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:47,070
Oh.
You're still on that?

292
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:48,240
Spike, listen!

293
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,730
How do I choose?

294
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:50,840
And when I do choose,

295
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,260
Will the other four
be mad at me?

296
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,910
I mean, I could give up
my ticket and give away two,

297
00:11:55,050 --> 00:11:57,180
But that would still leave
three disappointed ponies.

298
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:59,190
What if I --
Ah, your food.

299
00:11:59,450 --> 00:12:02,050
Oh, thank you.
This looks so good.

300
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:04,570
I'm sure everything will be
much clearer once I eat.

301
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:09,120
Um, madame?

302
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,820
Are you going to eat your food
in the rain?

303
00:12:12,010 --> 00:12:13,040
It's not raining.

304
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:16,060
[ Thunder rumbles ]

305
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:17,360
What's going on?

306
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:20,060
Hi, there, best friend forever
I've ever, ever had.

307
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:21,500
Enjoying
the sunny weather?

308
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:24,330
Rainbow Dash,
what are you doing?

309
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:25,520
What do you mean?

310
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,670
I just saw the smartest,

311
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:28,950
Most generous pony
about to get rained on,

312
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:30,640
So I thought
I'd kick a hole in the clouds

313
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:33,600
To keep her dry so she could
dine in peace, that's all.

314
00:12:33,860 --> 00:12:36,720
Rainbow, you're not trying
to get extra consideration

315
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:37,660
For the extra ticket

316
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:40,770
By doing me extra-Special
favors, are you?

317
00:12:40,820 --> 00:12:42,860
Me? No, no, no.

318
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:45,000
Of course not.
Uh-Huh.

319
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:48,020
Seriously,
I'd do it for anypony.

320
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:53,230
[ Gulps,
laughs nervously ]

321
00:12:53,570 --> 00:12:56,580
Rainbow, I am not comfortable
accepting unwanted favors,

322
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,530
So I'd appreciate it

323
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:59,410
If you'd close up
that rain cloud right now.

324
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,320
Ugh! Fine!

325
00:13:01,490 --> 00:13:02,050
[ Zip! ]

326
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:04,430
That's better.

327
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:09,380
[ Groans ]

328
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,550
Twilight!
It's raining.

329
00:13:13,810 --> 00:13:15,620
No, really?

330
00:13:15,810 --> 00:13:17,850
Come with me
before you catch a cold!

331
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:21,830
[ Whiffle! Whiffle! Whiffle! ]

332
00:13:22,570 --> 00:13:24,860
[ Laughs nervously ]
oops.

333
00:13:25,090 --> 00:13:25,960
Sorry.

334
00:13:26,910 --> 00:13:27,790
Oh, no!

335
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:29,530
It's quite all right!

336
00:13:29,820 --> 00:13:34,170
After all, we are the best
of friends, are we not?

337
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:37,350
And you know what
the best of friends do.

338
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:38,370
Uh...

339
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,660
makeover!

340
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:41,260
[ Grunting ]

341
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:42,850
Rarity! Ow!

342
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,050
This really
isn't necessary.

343
00:13:44,770 --> 00:13:46,090
I mean, thank you, but --
Ooh!

344
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,840
That's too tight!

345
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,140
[ Harp music plays ]

346
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,910
There!
Oh, you're simply darling!

347
00:13:53,230 --> 00:13:54,170
Uh...

348
00:13:54,280 --> 00:13:56,250
yeah, it is kind of pretty,
isn't it?

349
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,750
And you!

350
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:01,300
Oh, Spike, I have
a dandy little outfit

351
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:02,320
For the Dashing gent.

352
00:14:02,890 --> 00:14:06,690
Whoa! Ouch! Oh! Hey!
Come on! Watch it! Whoa!

353
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:09,440
[ Harpsichord music plays ]

354
00:14:10,110 --> 00:14:12,370
Oh, Spike.
Now you just need a hat.

355
00:14:12,490 --> 00:14:13,070
Ugh!

356
00:14:13,340 --> 00:14:15,920
I told you, I don't want any
part of this girly gala gunk.

357
00:14:16,030 --> 00:14:17,880
See you back at the library.
[ Zip! ]

358
00:14:17,980 --> 00:14:20,290
[ Laughs nervously ]
oh, who needs him anyway?

359
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:22,270
This is all about you

360
00:14:22,650 --> 00:14:25,710
And how fabulous you'll look
at the Grand Galloping Gala.

361
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:27,450
Wait.
The grand --

362
00:14:27,490 --> 00:14:28,180
[ Gasps ]

363
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:31,530
And, oh, my goodness.
What a coincidence.

364
00:14:31,650 --> 00:14:34,160
I happen to have an ensemble
of my own

365
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:35,940
That matches yours
to a "t."

366
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,570
We would be the belles
of the ball, you and i.

367
00:14:38,780 --> 00:14:41,000
Everyone would be clamoring
for our attention.

368
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,590
All eyes
would be on us.

369
00:14:42,860 --> 00:14:44,300
And then everyone
would finally know

370
00:14:44,470 --> 00:14:45,920
The most beautiful,
most talented,

371
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:48,220
Most sophisticated pony
in all of Equestria

372
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:50,530
Is Rarity the unicorn!

373
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,190
[ Giggles nervously ]

374
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,090
And Twilight Sparkle,
of course.

375
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:56,920
[ Giggles nervously ]

376
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:58,540
I see what's going on.

377
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:01,040
You're just buttering me up
so I give you the extra ticket.

378
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,450
Well,
it's not gonna work.

379
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,130
You're going to have to wait
for my decision

380
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,430
Just like everyone else.

381
00:15:05,590 --> 00:15:07,100
Now, if you'll excuse me,

382
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,470
I've been trying all day
just to get some lunch!

383
00:15:09,530 --> 00:15:11,750
Did somepony say "lunch"?

384
00:15:13,990 --> 00:15:15,870
You've got
to be kidding me!

385
00:15:16,060 --> 00:15:18,650
I got apple Pie,
apple fritters, apple tarts,

386
00:15:18,690 --> 00:15:20,840
Apple dumplings,
apple crisp, apple crumblers,

387
00:15:20,970 --> 00:15:23,680
And apple brown betty!

388
00:15:24,110 --> 00:15:26,140
Uh, the dessert,
not my auntie.

389
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,490
What do you say there,
best friend?

390
00:15:28,610 --> 00:15:29,980
[ Stomach grumbling ]

391
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,600
Is that a "yes"?

392
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,330
No. No!

393
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,440
I don't know
who I'm giving the ticket to!

394
00:15:36,700 --> 00:15:39,410
And all these favors aren't
making it any easier to decide.

395
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:42,620
In fact, I'm less sure now
than I was this morning!

396
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:43,820
Ugh!

397
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:45,500
So, that's a "maybe"?

398
00:15:49,380 --> 00:15:49,970
[ Sighs ]

399
00:15:50,010 --> 00:15:51,860
I never thought
being showered with favors

400
00:15:51,890 --> 00:15:53,210
Would be so aggravating!

401
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:59,870
[ Humming ]

402
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:02,820
[ Gasps ]
Fluttershy! Not you, too!

403
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,050
Oh!
Well, hello, Twilight.

404
00:16:05,330 --> 00:16:06,490
I hope you don't mind,

405
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:09,110
But we're all doing a little
spring cleaning for you.

406
00:16:09,290 --> 00:16:10,190
It's summer.

407
00:16:10,580 --> 00:16:11,090
Oh.

408
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:13,600
Well, better late
than never, right?

409
00:16:14,150 --> 00:16:15,990
It was Angel's idea.

410
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,000
[ Squeaks ]

411
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:20,670
You're not doing this
for the ticket, are you?

412
00:16:20,900 --> 00:16:22,060
Oh, no!

413
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:25,810
I'm doing this because
you're my very best friend,

414
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:26,780
Right, Angel?

415
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:28,600
Oh.

416
00:16:29,210 --> 00:16:31,640
Yes, we are just doing this
for the ticket.

417
00:16:32,220 --> 00:16:33,780
[ Stomach grumbling ]

418
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,810
No! No! No!

419
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:37,740
Well, this was all
very nice of you and Angel,

420
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:39,390
But I'm not accepting
any extra favors

421
00:16:39,420 --> 00:16:41,040
Until I've made
my final decision.

422
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,830
So I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

423
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,630
Surprise!
Surprise!
Surprise!
Surprise!

424
00:16:44,730 --> 00:16:45,690
[ Horns blowing ]

425
00:16:46,090 --> 00:16:47,520
* Twilight is
my bestest friend *

426
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:49,170
* whoopee, whoopee
Pinkie --

427
00:16:49,210 --> 00:16:51,890
* she's the cutest, smartest,
all-Around best pony, pony *

428
00:16:51,970 --> 00:16:55,070
Pinkie --
* I bet if I throw
a super-Duper fun party, party *

429
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:57,940
Pinkie!
* she'll give her extra ticket
to the gala to me *

430
00:16:57,980 --> 00:17:00,720
Pinkie!!

431
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:03,870
Yes, Twilight?

432
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:04,790
[ Blink! Blink! Blink! Blink! ]

433
00:17:05,430 --> 00:17:06,690
At least
the other ponies

434
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,830
Tried to be subtle
about the ticket.

435
00:17:08,990 --> 00:17:11,100
Wait, what ticket?
What gala?

436
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:12,130
Oh,
you didn't know?

437
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:14,990
Twilight has an extra ticket
to the Grand Galloping Gala!

438
00:17:15,170 --> 00:17:17,710
All:
the Grand Galloping Gala?!

439
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:19,900
Have I ever told you
how much I love your mane?

440
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:21,080
I'll wash your dishes.

441
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:23,100
Would you like any help
with your gardening?

442
00:17:23,550 --> 00:17:25,200
I have cartload
of extra carrots.

443
00:17:25,250 --> 00:17:27,440
[ All talking over each other ]

444
00:17:27,470 --> 00:17:28,710
What are we gonna do?

445
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:30,810
We're...gonna...

446
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:33,210
RUN!

447
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:12,700
[ All talking over each other ]

448
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:14,060
[ Ominous music plays ]

449
00:18:14,580 --> 00:18:15,650
[ All gasping ]

450
00:18:15,670 --> 00:18:16,890
Where is she?
Where did she go?

451
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:17,850
She's
disappeared!

452
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:19,650
[ Poof! ]

453
00:18:19,970 --> 00:18:20,880
[ Groans ]

454
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:23,950
Warn me next time
you're gonna do that.

455
00:18:24,130 --> 00:18:26,010
I didn't even know
it was gonna happen.

456
00:18:26,130 --> 00:18:27,500
Now quick --
Lock the doors!

457
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:28,550
[ Blows ]

458
00:18:33,300 --> 00:18:33,890
Whew.

459
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,140
[ Ominous music plays ]

460
00:18:36,170 --> 00:18:37,610
Yah!

461
00:18:37,730 --> 00:18:39,800
I can't decide!
I just can't decide!

462
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,230
It's important to all of you,

463
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:43,050
And I just can't stand
to disappoint any of you.

464
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:45,410
And giving me gifts and doing me
favors won't make any difference

465
00:18:45,610 --> 00:18:46,880
Because you're all
my friends,

466
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:48,360
And I want to make
you all happy.

467
00:18:48,390 --> 00:18:50,750
And I can't!
I just can't!

468
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:54,490
Twilight, sugar, I-I didn't mean
to put so much pressure on you.

469
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:57,900
And if it helps,
I don't want the ticket anymore.

470
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,820
You can give it
to somepony else.

471
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:01,770
I won't feel bad.
I promise.

472
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:02,790
Me too.

473
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:06,430
I feel just awful
that I made you feel so awful.

474
00:19:06,670 --> 00:19:09,680
And me too! It's no fun
upsetting your friends.

475
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:13,120
Twilight, it was unfair of me
to try to force you as I did.

476
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:16,780
Yes!
That means the ticket is mine!

477
00:19:16,830 --> 00:19:17,680
[ Laughs ]

478
00:19:17,740 --> 00:19:20,360
* I've got the ticket,
I've got the ticket *

479
00:19:23,340 --> 00:19:26,600
You know, I haven't
perfected my signature moves

480
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,930
For the Wonderbolts, anyway.

481
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,100
I don't need that ticket,
either.

482
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,990
We all got so gung ho
about going to the gala

483
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:36,250
That we couldn't see how
un-Gung ho we were making you.

484
00:19:36,690 --> 00:19:38,520
Together:
we're sorry, Twilight.

485
00:19:38,750 --> 00:19:40,400
Spike,
take down a note.

486
00:19:41,190 --> 00:19:42,640
"Dear princess Celestia,

487
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,750
"I've learned that one
of the joys of friendship

488
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,090
"Is sharing your blessings.

489
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:48,650
"But when there's not enough
blessings to go around,

490
00:19:48,730 --> 00:19:51,710
"Having more than your friends
can make you feel pretty awful.

491
00:19:52,050 --> 00:19:54,370
"So, though I appreciate
the invitation,

492
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:57,400
I will be returning both tickets
to the Grand Galloping Gala."

493
00:19:57,590 --> 00:19:58,400
What?!
What?!
What?!
What?!

494
00:19:58,510 --> 00:20:01,910
"If my friends can't all go,
I don't want to go, either."

495
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:05,570
Twilight, you don't
have to do that.

496
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:07,260
Nope.
I've made up my mind.

497
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:09,300
Spike, you can
send the letter now.

498
00:20:10,690 --> 00:20:11,150
[ Inhales deeply ]

499
00:20:11,230 --> 00:20:12,490
[ Exhales sharply ]

500
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:15,050
Now you won't get to go
to the gala, either.

501
00:20:15,210 --> 00:20:16,370
It's okay, girls.

502
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:18,030
I couldn't possibly enjoy myself

503
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:19,650
Without my best friends
there with me.

504
00:20:20,330 --> 00:20:21,630
[ All giggling ]

505
00:20:21,650 --> 00:20:23,250
So I would rather
not go at all.

506
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,130
[ Gagging ]

507
00:20:26,300 --> 00:20:28,110
Well, wallop
my withers, Spike.

508
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,820
Isn't that
just like a boy?

509
00:20:30,040 --> 00:20:32,000
Can't handle the least bit
of sentiment.

510
00:20:32,070 --> 00:20:33,740
[ Burps ]
whoa, nelly!

511
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:34,960
[ Poof! ]

512
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:38,000
A letter from the princess?
That was fast.

513
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:40,390
"My faithful student
Twilight,

514
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:43,100
Why didn't you just say so
in the first place?"

515
00:20:44,220 --> 00:20:46,470
Six tickets
to the Grand Galloping Gala!

516
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:47,630
[ All gasping ]

517
00:20:47,890 --> 00:20:49,380
Now we can all go!

518
00:20:49,610 --> 00:20:52,490
[ All cheering ]

519
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,050
[ Stomach grumbling ]

520
00:20:54,270 --> 00:20:55,310
[ Laughs nervously ]

521
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,310
Allow us
to treat you to dinner.

522
00:20:58,030 --> 00:20:59,860
What a great way
to apologize.

523
00:20:59,910 --> 00:21:01,640
And to celebrate!

524
00:21:01,690 --> 00:21:04,330
Come on, everyone!
The cupcakes are on me!

525
00:21:07,460 --> 00:21:09,920
How come I don't get a ticket
to the gala?

526
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,030
[ Gasps ]

527
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:12,370
[ Burps ]

528
00:21:13,420 --> 00:21:14,880
"And one for you, Spike."

529
00:21:15,850 --> 00:21:18,270
[ Giggling ]

530
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:21,000
I mean, gross!

531
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:22,470
I have to go, too?

532
00:21:24,370 --> 00:21:28,350
[ Zip! ]
[ Both laugh ]

